# The recipe copies, but realising its inputs partly fails: some outputs aren't
# in any cache (excluded assembly-tower leaves, or a path whose closure is
# incomplete). The box never builds, so an incomplete tree is expected — the gen
# must still count as mirrored (recorded seen, exit 0), not fail+retry forever.
# Stubs: fake copy/realise/flock + a nix-store that answers the (non-seam)
# --query --references call.
# Re-runnable: after the first run the gen is seen, so re-runs hit "no new roots"
# and still exit 0; stdout is not asserted for that reason.
KASHA_REMOTE=s3://cache
KASHA_FLAKE=znix
KASHA_STATE_DIR=/tmp/kasha-mirror-down-partial-fixture
KASHA_LIST_FILE=tests/fixtures/mirror-down/partial-tree/list
KASHA_MANIFEST_DIR=tests/fixtures/mirror-down/partial-tree/manifests
KASHA_COPY=true
KASHA_REALISE=fake-realise
